      "y": 1930.4635059217471,
      "width": 680,
      "height": 187.5,
      "strokeColor": "#0F172A",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "roundness": null,
      "text": "With 100K workflows and 1M runs/day, what does that imply for QPS and concurrency?\n\nRoughly ~10 new workflow starts/sec on average.\n\n• Baseline ingest ≈ 10 QPS\n• Peak ≈ 100 QPS (10× burst)\n• If runs average ~1 min → ~600 concurrent\n• At peak, design toward up to ~60K concurrent\n\nWe must account for disk I/O, concurrency control, and reliability under load.",
      "fontSize": 15,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "With 100K workflows and 1M runs/day, what does that imply for QPS and concurrency?\n\nRoughly ~10 new workflow starts/sec on average.\n\n• Baseline ingest ≈ 10 QPS\n• Peak ≈ 100 QPS (10× burst)\n• If runs average ~1 min → ~600 concurrent\n• At peak, design toward up to ~60K concurrent\n\nWe must account for disk I/O, concurrency control, and reliability under load.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "version": 108,
      "index": "b6e"
    },
